            "id": "intro_math_operations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Basic Math Operations",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Python can perform basic mathematical calculations just like a calculator. We can add, subtract, multiply, and divide numbers."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "basic_arithmetic",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Basic Arithmetic",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Python uses the same symbols we use in math: `+` for addition, `-` for subtraction, `*` for multiplication, and `/` for division."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "print(5 + 3)\nprint(10 - 4)\nprint(6 * 2)\nprint(15 / 3)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "8\n6\n12\n5.0"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "modulus_operation",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "We can also find the remainder after division using modulus `%`. The **modulus operator** returns the remainder of the division of two numbers."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "result = 11 % 5\nprint(result)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "1"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "exponentiation_operation",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "And there's also the exponentiation operator `**`. It raises a number to the power of another number."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "result = 2 ** 3\nprint(result)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "8"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
